1
00:01:11,052 --> 00:01:12,131
Are you ready?

2
00:01:13,842 --> 00:01:14,262
Your Majesty

3
00:01:14,672 --> 00:01:15,212
What's wrong?

4
00:01:15,922 --> 00:01:16,922
We can't swim

5
00:01:17,302 --> 00:01:19,092
If there is an accident

6
00:01:20,302 --> 00:01:21,262
This makes sense

7
00:01:21,552 --> 00:01:22,921
But in order to return to Southern Kingdom,

8
00:01:22,922 --> 00:01:24,092
we must try

9
00:01:24,712 --> 00:01:25,342
Your Majesty

10
00:01:25,672 --> 00:01:26,802
What's wrong again?

11
00:01:27,462 --> 00:01:28,672
I have another method

12
00:01:33,712 --> 00:01:34,842
Will this method work?

13
00:01:35,212 --> 00:01:36,052
Don't worry, Your Majesty

14
00:01:36,262 --> 00:01:37,212
It's a smaller version

15
00:01:37,302 --> 00:01:38,462
The effect should be similar

16
00:02:00,462 --> 00:02:01,462
What was that sound?

17
00:02:03,762 --> 00:02:04,962
Mr. Ye is testing the water for us

18
00:02:15,212 --> 00:02:16,632
There is no Imperial Physician here

19
00:02:17,052 --> 00:02:18,092
What should we do?

20
00:02:26,762 --> 00:02:28,092
I may need

21
00:02:28,092 --> 00:02:29,262
artificial respiration

22
00:02:30,512 --> 00:02:32,881
What is artificial respiration?

23
00:02:33,632 --> 00:02:35,132
I know. Let me do it

24
00:02:48,712 --> 00:02:49,462
Why am I here?

25
00:02:50,632 --> 00:02:51,592
Why am I here?

26
00:02:52,842 --> 00:02:53,631
So cold

27
00:02:55,882 --> 00:02:58,172
The second method is soul travel by electric shock

28
00:03:03,592 --> 00:03:04,171
We did it

29
00:03:04,762 --> 00:03:05,462
Yes

30
00:03:05,922 --> 00:03:07,632
Wuming, what did you see?

31
00:03:07,882 --> 00:03:09,712
Back to Your Majesty, darkness

32
00:03:14,212 --> 00:03:14,922
What are you doing?

33
00:03:21,132 --> 00:03:22,212
Are you ready, Your Majesty?

34
00:03:22,882 --> 00:03:23,672
Ready

35
00:03:24,132 --> 00:03:26,462
One, two, three

36
00:03:28,132 --> 00:03:28,962
Don't jump, both of you

37
00:03:35,212 --> 00:03:36,052
You are

38
00:03:36,882 --> 00:03:38,552
You are tired of living?

39
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:39,762
You're really not afraid of death

40
00:03:40,052 --> 00:03:42,212
If I hadn't rushed out, you must have gone to the heaven

41
00:03:42,212 --> 00:03:43,512
instead of Southern Kingdom

42
00:03:43,762 --> 00:03:45,212
<i>We</i> are the empress of a country

43
00:03:45,672 --> 00:03:47,262
A country cannot be without a ruler for a day

44
00:03:47,922 --> 00:03:49,052
The court is unstable now

45
00:03:49,672 --> 00:03:50,842
If some vicious one...

46
00:03:51,092 --> 00:03:52,421
I deserve death

47
00:03:53,092 --> 00:03:55,012
I shouldn't let Your Majesty take the risk

48
00:03:55,632 --> 00:03:57,672
Thanks to Mr. Ye for risking his life to save us

49
00:03:58,212 --> 00:03:58,962
I'm...

50
00:03:59,462 --> 00:04:01,382
Okay, okay, please

51
00:04:02,632 --> 00:04:04,052
You are still the general who protects the country

52
00:04:06,052 --> 00:04:07,342
You're asking for death

53
00:04:07,712 --> 00:04:08,552
But isn't this

54
00:04:09,002 --> 00:04:10,422
the method you told us?

55
00:04:11,672 --> 00:04:12,462
Maybe,

56
00:04:12,712 --> 00:04:14,302
maybe the time is wrong

57
00:04:14,762 --> 00:04:16,922
Time, oh, Your Majesty

58
00:04:17,052 --> 00:04:19,212
Our incident happened on the day you ascended the throne

59
00:04:19,422 --> 00:04:21,262
That day happened to be the Double Seventh Festival

60
00:04:24,882 --> 00:04:26,422
If it really doesn't work,

61
00:04:26,632 --> 00:04:28,132
you can also stay here

62
00:04:28,632 --> 00:04:30,172
Can I let you guys starve?

63
00:04:49,962 --> 00:04:50,882
Chen

64
00:04:51,092 --> 00:04:53,262
You've been so emotionally unstable lately

65
00:04:53,262 --> 00:04:54,672
Is there something you are hiding from me?

66
00:04:55,512 --> 00:04:56,422
Nothing

67
00:04:57,422 --> 00:04:58,842
If we really can't go back,

68
00:04:59,052 --> 00:04:59,881
what should we do?

69
00:05:00,212 --> 00:05:01,012
I'll follow Your Majesty

70
00:05:01,262 --> 00:05:01,962
wherever you go

71
00:05:03,632 --> 00:05:05,092
If we really can't go back

72
00:05:25,672 --> 00:05:27,422
Miss, do we know each other?

73
00:05:30,882 --> 00:05:31,712
You look

74
00:05:31,712 --> 00:05:33,422
like an older brother in <i>Our</i> family

75
00:05:33,882 --> 00:05:35,802
But he won't smile at <i>Us</i> like this

76
00:05:37,342 --> 00:05:38,921
Hello, I'm Li Tianxing

77
00:05:39,302 --> 00:05:40,002
Hong Dou

78
00:05:40,712 --> 00:05:41,512
Good day, boss

79
00:05:41,882 --> 00:05:42,762
This is my assistant

80
00:05:53,132 --> 00:05:54,592
You, come with me

81
00:05:54,592 --> 00:05:55,671
You, stay here

82
00:06:07,842 --> 00:06:09,262
Why do you like to flirt so much?

83
00:06:10,012 --> 00:06:11,712
Flirt with who?

84
00:06:12,012 --> 00:06:13,552
A wooden head and a man with glasses

85
00:06:15,012 --> 00:06:16,342
Are you jealous?

86
00:06:16,632 --> 00:06:17,422
Jealous?

87
00:06:21,052 --> 00:06:21,881
Who do you think you are?

88
00:06:21,882 --> 00:06:23,302
You are just an assistant

89
00:06:25,632 --> 00:06:26,422
Then why

90
00:06:27,212 --> 00:06:28,342
do you care

91
00:06:28,342 --> 00:06:29,711
what <i>We</i> did so much

92
00:06:30,422 --> 00:06:31,712
I'm just worried

93
00:06:32,052 --> 00:06:33,262
Leaving the wooden man aside first,

94
00:06:33,882 --> 00:06:34,382
the one wearing glasses

95
00:06:34,382 --> 00:06:35,632
is not a good person at all

96
00:06:39,132 --> 00:06:40,172
Oh. You just responded with an "Oh"?

97
00:06:40,842 --> 00:06:42,262
Do you understand what I'm saying?

98
00:06:42,262 --> 00:06:43,212
Do you remember my words?

99
00:06:43,212 --> 00:06:43,672
In this world,

100
00:06:43,672 --> 00:06:45,212
there are more bad people than good people

101
00:06:45,262 --> 00:06:45,712
What's more,

102
00:06:45,712 --> 00:06:47,512
you look like a naive little bunny without any social experience
